    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Carbon Black Metallic, representing the pinnacle of the S54-powered era. This specimen features the iconic 3.2L naturally aspirated straight-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a recalibrated dual-VANOS system for razor-sharp throttle response and an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential lock, ensuring optimal power delivery to the rear wheels. Mechanically, this unit is flawless: the critical rod bearing service has been performed, and the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced to exceed factory specifications. The suspension remains tight, retaining its original geometry with zero bushing deflection. With pristine paint depth and an interior free of bolster wear, this is a concours-level example for the serious collector seeking mechanical purity.",
